1 AN ACT concerning water; establishing the water program task force to
2 evaluate the state's water program and funding for such program;
3 requiring a report thereon to the legislature and the governor.
4
5 Be it enacted by the Legislature of the State of Kansas:
6 Section 1. (a) There is hereby established the water program task
7 force. The task force shall consist of:
8 (1) The following 29 voting members:
9 (A) The chair of the house of representatives committee on water;
10 (B) the chair of the house of representatives committee on agriculture
11 and natural resources;
12 (C) the chair of the house of representatives committee on
13 appropriations;
14 (D) the chair of the senate committee on agriculture and natural
15 resources;
16 (E) the chair of the senate committee on ways and means;
17 (F) the ranking minority member of the house of representatives
18 committee on water;
19 (G) the ranking minority member of the senate agriculture and natural
20 resources committee;
21 (H) one member of the house of representatives appointed by the
22 speaker of the house of representatives;
23 (I) one Kansas resident appointed by the speaker of the house of
24 representatives;
25 (J) one member of the house of representatives appointed by the
26 speaker pro tem;
27 (K) one Kansas resident appointed by the speaker pro tem;
28 (L) one member of the house of representatives appointed by the
29 house minority leader;
